2026-04-16 07:53:42 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Control Module Switch'] hypothesis_explanation="The resistance measurement across the closed control switch is extremely high (1 GΩ), indicating that the switch is not providing proper electrical contact in the 'on' (closed) position. This prevents 12V from passing through to the load module and thus the lamp does not turn on, even though there is proper voltage at the input to the control module. There are no observed wiring or component damages, and all voltages and polarity checks are consistent with nominal operation except at the switch output. Therefore, the switch in the control module is the likely root cause."
