description: Measure the voltage at the input side (power supply side) of the control module when the switch is operated to verify if 12V is present at the control module input. This will help determine if the issue lies between the power supply and the control module., outcome="The 'Control Input Cable (+)' is at 11.99 V and the 'Control Input Cable (−)' is at 0.0 V, both referenced to ground. No polarity inversion is detected; the measured voltages are consistent with expected positive and negative connections at the control module input.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Observe -> Control module (switch mechanism and internal circuit),
description: Open the bottom of the control module and visually inspect the switch wiring and internal connections for any loose wires, broken solder joints, or obvious component damage., outcome='No loose wires or component damage were observed. The Control Switch has a high internal resistance and is closed. No POLARITY INVERSION detected in any inspected cable connections.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=95.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Control Module Switch,
description: Test the continuity and resistance across the closed control switch with a multimeter to determine if it is making proper electrical contact when in the 'on' position., outcome="The test shows that the control switch, when closed, still has an open circuit with a measured resistance of 1,000,000,000 Ω instead of the nominal 0.01 Ω. This indicates the switch is not making proper electrical contact in the 'on' position.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=30.0, cost_breakdown=[('close_switch', 10.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
